{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01DbNkRKm3QFMa73cHQNspUX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pod is crashing again. The plugin installation inside the pod didn't persist because it's installed in the ephemeral filesystem. When the pod restarts, the filesystem is reset and the plugin is no longer installed. So my approach of installing the plugin in the running container won't work for restarts.\n\nI need a different approach. The plugin needs to be persistent. Options:\n1. Use an init container that installs the plugin before Elasticsearch starts\n2. Use a custom Docker image with the plugin pre-installed\n3. Install the plugin in a persistent volume\n\nThe best approach for a Kubernetes StatefulSet is to use an init container. The init container would:\n1. Copy the existing plugins directory content to a shared volume\n2. Install the repository plugin into that shared volume\n3. The main container then mounts this shared volume as its plugins directory\n\nI'll set up an `emptyDir` volume for the plugins and configure an init container with the same Elasticsearch image to handle the plugin installation before the main container starts.\n\nThe tricky part is that the init container needs to install the plugin directly to the shared volume mount point, not to its local filesystem. So I'll mount the shared plugins volume in both containers and ensure the installation targets that mounted path.\n\nUpdating the StatefulSet with the init container...\n\nI need to be careful here since the StatefulSet already has existing volume mounts for the config and data. I'm adding the plugins volume as an emptyDir and mounting it in both the init container and the main container so the installed plugin persists across container restarts. Then I'll use kubectl to patch the StatefulSet with these changes.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":557,"cache_read_input_tokens":50471,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":557},"output_tokens":21,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5ac5cff4-d409-4ac3-8f10-c278d889fd74","uuid":"f4bb0459-5e26-4cc7-b871-9befd197e128","request_id":"req_011CcLR4q5t8YU624Qgtk6VW"}
