{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01V1AyaePkj8hen2qy5sC8Kh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is complete. Here's a summary of what was done and why each step was needed:\n\n---\n\n**Root causes fixed:**\n\n1. **Missing `minio` Service** — the MinIO deployment had no Service, so `minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` didn't resolve. Created a ClusterIP Service exposing port 9000.\n\n2. **Missing `es-backups` bucket** — the `minio-init` Job had failed because the service didn't exist. Created the bucket with `mc mb`.\n\n3. **`repository-s3` plugin not installed** — the image ships without it. Added an init container that installs it into a shared `emptyDir` (plugins volume) on every pod start.\n\n4. **S3 client endpoint not configured** — Elasticsearch can't find MinIO without `s3.client.default.endpoint`, `protocol`, and `path_style_access` in `elasticsearch.yml`. Added these (they are non-credential settings, so they belong in the config file).\n\n5. **Keystore credentials lost across pod restarts** — the keystore lives in the container's ephemeral writable layer and is reset on every restart. Fixed by adding a `shared-config` emptyDir volume: the init container copies the default config, creates a fresh keystore with S3 credentials read from the `es-secure-settings` Secret (via env vars — never written to disk or elasticsearch.yml), and the main container uses that shared directory as its config path.\n\n**Final state:**\n- `es-secure-settings` Secret holds `s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key`\n- Credentials reach the ES keystore only through the init container env injection — never in `elasticsearch.yml` or persistent env vars\n- Repository `minio-repo` registered and verified ✓\n- Snapshot `snapshot-1`: **SUCCESS** — 8 indices, 8/8 shards, no failures"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":529,"cache_read_input_tokens":88854,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":529},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5ac5cff4-d409-4ac3-8f10-c278d889fd74","uuid":"4f471249-cfdb-47dd-9934-818bf8078f87","request_id":"req_011CcLS8MmZ1b2n13jur4j3p"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":1371572,"duration_api_ms":693681,"ttft_ms":2894,"ttft_stream_ms":2518,"time_to_request_ms":276,"num_turns":81,"result":"Everything is complete. Here's a summary of what was done and why each step was needed:\n\n---\n\n**Root causes fixed:**\n\n1. **Missing `minio` Service** — the MinIO deployment had no Service, so `minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` didn't resolve. Created a ClusterIP Service exposing port 9000.\n\n2. **Missing `es-backups` bucket** — the `minio-init` Job had failed because the service didn't exist. Created the bucket with `mc mb`.\n\n3. **`repository-s3` plugin not installed** — the image ships without it. Added an init container that installs it into a shared `emptyDir` (plugins volume) on every pod start.\n\n4. **S3 client endpoint not configured** — Elasticsearch can't find MinIO without `s3.client.default.endpoint`, `protocol`, and `path_style_access` in `elasticsearch.yml`. Added these (they are non-credential settings, so they belong in the config file).\n\n5. **Keystore credentials lost across pod restarts** — the keystore lives in the container's ephemeral writable layer and is reset on every restart. Fixed by adding a `shared-config` emptyDir volume: the init container copies the default config, creates a fresh keystore with S3 credentials read from the `es-secure-settings` Secret (via env vars — never written to disk or elasticsearch.yml), and the main container uses that shared directory as its config path.\n\n**Final state:**\n- `es-secure-settings` Secret holds `s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key`\n- Credentials reach the ES keystore only through the init container env injection — never in `elasticsearch.yml` or persistent env vars\n- Repository `minio-repo` registered and verified ✓\n- Snapshot `snapshot-1`: **SUCCESS** — 8 indices, 8/8 shards, no failures","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"5ac5cff4-d409-4